# ========================================
# DEVELOPMENT CONFIGURATION
# ========================================
# These are configured in the application code, not as environment variables

# Database Configuration
# - All database settings are in supabase/config.toml
# - Connection details managed by Supabase integration

# Application Settings
# - Debug mode: Controlled by logger configuration
# - Feature flags: Defined in constants files
# - API endpoints: Auto-generated from Supabase

# ========================================
# PRODUCTION CHECKLIST
# ========================================
# Before deploying to production, ensure:
# 
# 1. All required secrets are set in Supabase dashboard
# 2. Email templates are configured (if using email features)
# 3. Domain and CORS settings are updated in Supabase
# 4. Database RLS policies are properly configured
# 5. Rate limiting is configured for edge functions
# 6. Backup and monitoring systems are in place
# 7. SSL certificates are configured for custom domains

# ========================================
# ADDING NEW SECRETS
# ========================================
# To add a new secret:
# 
# 1. In Lovable chat, ask for the feature that requires the secret
# 2. AI will provide a lov-secret-form action to add it securely
# 3. Secret will be available in edge functions as Deno.env.get('SECRET_NAME')
# 4. Never commit actual secret values to version control
# 5. Update this example file with the new secret name and description

# ========================================
# TROUBLESHOOTING
# ========================================
# Common issues and solutions:
#
# Issue: "Environment variable not found"
# Solution: Add the secret through Supabase dashboard or lov-secret-form
#
# Issue: "Database connection failed"
# Solution: Check Supabase project status and connection settings
#
# Issue: "Auth errors in development"
# Solution: Verify Supabase auth providers are configured correctly
#
# Issue: "Functions not working"
# Solution: Check edge function logs in Supabase dashboard

# ========================================
# SECURITY NOTES
# ========================================
# - Never commit actual environment variables to git
# - Use strong, unique values for all secrets
# - Rotate secrets regularly, especially for production
# - Limit secret access to necessary team members only
# - Monitor secret usage through Supabase logs
# - Use different secrets for different environments
